{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "14", "m": "11", "Y": "2025"}, "time": {"H": "10", "M": "12", "S": "00"}}, "news": [{"title": "Mysuru civic body to intensify ward-wise e-khata issuance drive", "para": "Mysuru City Corporation is intensifying its e-khata property document issuance drive across all nine wards to achieve 100% coverage of 2,27,883 properties. So far, 61,117 e-khatas have been issued, with the drive set to resume next Friday after a temporary slowdown. Nodal officers are appointed to monitor progress, aiming for issuance within three to four days of application.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/mysuru-city-corporation-to-boost-e-khata-issuance-for-property-owners/125319139?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-33350/125319139.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Pune: Residents, environmentalists raise concerns over RMC plant near Pashan Lake", "para": "Residents and environmentalists in Pune are raising concerns over a proposed ready-mix concrete plant near Pashan Lake. They fear particulate matter emissions will harm local and migratory birds, and potentially worsen the lake's existing pollution. Concerns also include respiratory diseases for nearby residents and adverse effects on the local ecosystem.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/cement/residents-alarmed-as-controversial-rmc-plant-planned-near-pashan-lake/125319109?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-70556/125319109.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "cement"}, {"title": "Hyderabad: HYDRAA faces 700 cases after saving 1,000 acres", "para": "Hyderabad's asset protection agency, HYDRAA, faces nearly 700 lawsuits after reclaiming public properties worth Rs 55,000 crore. Despite legal challenges and accusations of overstepping, officials remain confident in their mission to protect public and environmental assets, stating they operate within legal frameworks.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/hyderabad-hydraa-faces-700-cases-after-saving-1000-acres/125319076?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-60772/125319076.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}]}